text:p.text:span: All BPMN gallery items has styles support so the shapes will follow the Default and Accent 2 style from your draw/impress template.
Users can change the BPMN diagram by edit Default and Accent 2 style.
BPMN gallery items use 11px font size to fit well in writer and draw. Bold borders have 0,10 mm line width.
As all LibreOffice gallery items the BPMN symbols fit perfect into the default grid
gallery items store the styles as direct formatting style, so when you move an gallery item into the page click Format Clear Direct Formatting and the gallery items use the defined styles.
you can play around with Default and Accent 2 style to get nice symbols for example
Untyped events, indicate start point, state of changes or final states
Cyclic timer events, points in time, time spans, or timeouts
Escalating to a higher level of responsibility
Reacting to changed business conditions or integrating business rules
Off-page connectors. Two corresponding link events equal a sequence flow
Reacting to cancelled transactions or triggering cancellations
Signaling across diff. processes. A signal thrown can be caught multiple times
Catching one out of a set of events. Throwing all events defined
Catching all out of a set of parallel events
Triggering the immediate termination of a process
routes sequence flow to a precise outgoing branch.
waits for one incoming branch to finish before triggering an otugoing flow.
A gateway is represented with a diamond shape and determines forking and merging of paths, depending on the conditions expressed.
One or more branches are activated when splitting. All active incoming branches must complete before merging.
the gateway waits for all incoming branches to finish before triggering outgoing flow
Gateways that represent actions not capture by other gateways. Can be complex, merging or branching actions/behaviors.
Each occurrence of a subsequent event starts a new process instant.
Two parallel processes are started based on an event, but there is no evaluation of the event.
The condition determining the path of a process is based on an evaluated event.
is an atomic activity within a process flow. A task is used when the work in a process cannot be broken down into finer levels of detail
is a specialized type of sub-process whose special behavior is controlled through a transaction protocol.
may occur many times. Unlike the standard SubProcess that uses the flow of the parent process as a trigger, it has a Start Event as a trigger.
is used to group different activities but does not affect the flow in the diagram
identies a point in a process where a global process is used. The Call Activity acts as a wrapper for the invocation of the global process within the execution.
specify the nature of the action to be preformed.
element can optionally reference a Data State element, which is the state of data contained in a Data Object
is an external input for the whole process
is a data result of the whole process
provides a mechanism for activities to retrieve or update stored information that will persist beyond the scope of a process
